result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs, PAC>=0.08, <0.15 (1st). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs, PAC>=0.08, <0.15 (1st) was dismissed by the court.

  • Stephanie M Groth was found guilty of OWI (1st w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Stephanie M Groth in court with attorney Jeremy Evans for attorney Matthew Mckenzie Murray.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant entered a plea of guilty to count 1. Court found defendant guilty of count 1.
Count 2 dismissed and read-in and count 3 dismissed outright by operation of law. 

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

HUBER:  30 days, w/Standard Release Conditions (Credit - 1 day). Defendant to report to Huber facility by 7:00 p.m. on February 10, 2017. Sentence may be served in Washington County. Defendant has 12 hour shifts and will need approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours for a total up to 15 hours per day if defendant serves sentence in Waukesha County. 

FINE: $1229.00 to be paid at a rate of $100.00/month commencing May 1, 2017 or alternate driver license suspension, as penalty for non payment of fine; APPLY CASH BAIL.

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 to be paid at $100.00 month consecutive to payment of fine or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of surcharge.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $50.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Village of Eagle Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

D/L REVOCATION: 14 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 14 months;

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
